Chapter 2: Who Are the Neighboring Societies?
Core Question
Who else is building nearby or around shared purpose?
Understand
Federation begins with discovery.
Not everyone doing good work is ready to federate.
Not every group should be connected immediately.
The society should identify other circles, associations, churches, family funds, neighborhood groups, business groups, preparedness circles, youth groups, property stewardship groups, and mutual aid societies that may share values.
Some may be formal.
Some may be informal.
Some may already use Simba.
Some may not.
Discovery should be respectful.
The goal is not to recruit people into a brand.
The goal is to learn who is building and whether shared infrastructure would help.
The first stage of federation is relationship, not agreement.
Discuss
Who else is doing aligned work?
Who has trust in their local circle?
Who has records and structure?
Who is still informal but serious?
Who should we learn from?
Who should we approach carefully?
What relationship already exists?
