PART TWO: BUILD SHARED INFRASTRUCTURE

Chapter 5: Create Shared Templates
Core Question
What tools should every society be able to use without starting from scratch?
Understand
Federation should reduce duplication.
Every society should not have to reinvent the same worksheets, policies, reports, and meeting structures.
Shared templates help societies build faster without skipping formation.
Templates may include:
Start a Society checklist
 Blueprint Audit
 First Ten worksheet
 Purpose Builder
 Covenant
 Treasury Setup
 Ledger categories
 Needs Map
 Skills and Assets Map
 Care Team template
 Rules Builder
 Meeting agenda
 100-Day Plan
 Day 100 Report
 Recommitment Check
 Next Phase Plan
 Repair process
 New member orientation
 Business campaign plan
 Property records checklist
 Preparedness plan
 Youth mentorship plan
 Ecosystem Report
 Wealth Circulation Report
 Property Stewardship Report
Templates should guide, not control.
Local societies should adapt them while preserving minimum standards.
Discuss
What templates helped us most?
What did we have to create from scratch?
What should new societies receive immediately?
What templates need local customization?
How do we prevent templates from replacing real discussion?
