Chapter 6: Create Shared Training
Core Question
What should every society learn before carrying more responsibility?
Understand
Training is one of the most important federation functions.
A federation should help societies learn without making each society dependent on one leader.
Shared training may include:
How to start a society
 How to run meetings
 How to keep a ledger
 How to protect privacy
 How to handle aid requests
 How to build care teams
 How to write rules
 How to repair conflict
 How to train youth
 How to support businesses
 How to protect property
 How to prepare for emergencies
 How to produce reports
 How to prevent extraction
 How to form leadership benches
 How to use Simba
Training should be practical.
Every session should produce a worksheet, decision, role, report, or action.
No training should end with inspiration only.
Discuss
What training would have helped us earlier?
What do new societies need first?
What training should be required?
What training should be repeated quarterly?
Who can teach from lived practice?
How will training be documented?
