Chapter 8: Build the Regional Dashboard
Core Question
How do we see regional strength without exposing local dignity?
Understand
A regional dashboard helps societies see collective movement.
It should show patterns, not private details.
A dashboard can reveal:
How many societies are active
 Where needs repeat
 Which businesses are being supported
 Where youth training is happening
 Where property risks are rising
 Where preparedness is weak
 Which societies need support
 Which societies can mentor others
 Where money is circulating
 Where reports are missing
 Where leadership roles are vacant
 Where shared training is needed
The dashboard should not become surveillance.
It should not shame societies.
It should not expose private hardship.
It should help the federation direct support.
The dashboard is a mirror, not a weapon.
Discuss
What regional patterns do we need to see?
What data should remain local?
How should struggling societies be supported?
What dashboard alerts would be helpful?
What dashboard alerts could be harmful?
Who can view the regional dashboard?
