Chapter 14: Federation Treasury Standards
Core Question
How do we handle shared money across societies?
Understand
Federation money requires extra care.
Money across societies can create confusion, suspicion, and conflict if rules are unclear.
The federation should define whether it will hold shared funds.
If yes, it needs:
Purpose
 Contribution model
 Treasurer
 Assistant treasurer
 Approval rule
 Reserve rule
 Ledger
 Reporting rhythm
 Participating societies
 Distribution rules
 Conflict of interest standards
 Audit or review process
 Privacy standards
A federation should not collect shared money until local societies understand the rules.
Shared money must have shared memory.
Discuss
Do we need federation-level funds now?
What would the fund be for?
Who contributes?
Who approves use?
How are reports shared?
How do we avoid one society carrying another unfairly?
How do we protect trust?
Build: Federation Treasury Standards
