Chapter 17: Federation Report
Core Question
What did we build together that none of us could build alone?
Understand
The Federation Report should show what shared infrastructure made possible.
It should not erase local stories.
It should include both network-level metrics and local society highlights.
The report should answer:
How many societies participated?
What standards were shared?
What trainings were completed?
What campaigns were coordinated?
What money or value circulated regionally?
What businesses were supported?
What property risks were addressed?
What youth were trained?
What preparedness improved?
What reports were completed?
What conflicts were repaired?
What privacy was protected?
